<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>THANN:  True.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>KIRK:  Then you cannot let him die.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>LAL:  His death is not important. We must wait to see whether her instinct for self-sacrifice has become stronger than her instinct for self-preservation.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: McCoy starts to wake. Gem returns to him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Don't touch me. Stay away. Jim. Spock. Are you here?</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, Bones.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Don't let her touch me. She'll die. Jim, I can't destroy life, even if it's to save my own. I can't. You know that. I can't let you do it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: McCoy pushes Gem away.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>KIRK:  What is it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>SPOCK:  The intensity of emotion is draining us and building up the force field.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, I know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>SPOCK:  It draws its energy from us, Captain. In spite of what we see, all emotion must be suppressed. That might weaken the field.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>KIRK:  I'll try.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock leaves the forcefield, but Kirk remains trapped.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>(Spock takes the device from Thann, and Kirk is free too.) KIRK:  Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>LAL:  You cannot use our powers to change what is happening.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>KIRK:  You must save the life of our friend.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>LAL:  No. We will not. Her instinct must be developed to the fullest. The test must be complete.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>SPOCK:  It is complete. Gem has earned the right of survival for her planet. She offered her life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>LAL:  To offer is not proof enough.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>KIRK:  If death is all you understand, here are four lives for you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk returns the two devices.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>KIRK:  We will not leave our friend. You've lost the capacity to feel the emotions you brought Gem here to experience. You don't understand what it is to live. Love and compassion are dead in you. You're nothing but intellect.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Lal goes over to McCoy and heals him, then picks up the unconscious Gem.</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>LAL:  Farewell.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They recede into the darkness.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>KIRK:  Strange.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>SPOCK:  What is puzzling you, Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>KIRK:  I'm not puzzled, Mister Spock. I am awed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I'm with you, Captain. She awed me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>KIRK:  No, no. I wasn't thinking of Gem. I was thinking of that fantastic element of chance that out in limitless space we should come together with Gem.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Captain, the element of chance can virtually be eliminated by a civilisation as advanced as the Vians.</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Not to dispute your computer, Mister Spock, but from little what you've told me, I would say she was a pearl of great price.</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>KIRK:  What, Scott?</td></tr>

<tr id="L359"><td><a href="#L359">359</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Do you not know the story of the merchant? The merchant, who when he found one pearl of great price, went and sold all that he had and bought it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, she was all that. And whether the Vians bought her or found her makes little difference. She was of great value.</td></tr>

<tr id="L361"><td><a href="#L361">361</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Well, personally, I find it fascinating that with all their scientific knowledge and advances, that it was good old-fashioned human emotion that they valued the most.</td></tr>

<tr id="L362"><td><a href="#L362">362</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Perhaps the Vulcans should hear about this.</td></tr>

<tr id="L363"><td><a href="#L363">363</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Spock, can you be prevailed upon to bring them the news?</td></tr>

<tr id="L364"><td><a href="#L364">364</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Possibly, Captain. I shall certainly give the thought all the consideration it is due.</td></tr>

